One issue is that the server uses Google Protocol Buffers. The following definition, for instance:<p><pre><code>    message Foo {
	required string a = 1;
	required int32 b = 2;
	optional int64 c = 3;
    }
</code></pre>
Generates a struct like:<p><pre><code>    type Foo struct {
        a *string
        b *int32
        c *int64
    }
</code></pre>
This is not particularly friendly to the garbage collector compared to a POD struct with no pointers.
